    "Abdullah et al. [81] reported that POFA at 20% replacement improves the interfacial transition zone (ITZ) between aggregates and cement paste, strengthening bonds and reducing weaknesses.",
    "Kamaruddin et al. [27] noted that treated POFA (T-POFA) further enhances microstructural density by reducing calcium hydroxide and promoting durable C-S-H gel formation.",
    "As indicated in Fig. 10, the SEM photo displays the effect of POFA on the concrete microstructure.",
    "BentoniteYang et al. [85] reported a 76.47% increase in impermeability due to bentonite's effectiveness in reducing pore size and connectivity.",
    "Memon et al. [84] found that bentonite decreases porosity and enhances acid resistance, showing a 10-15% reduction in weight loss compared to the control."
